  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nAccording to Discord report:\r\n\"Runnning OOM eventually on every machine I use. Prev I used 24gb node and was hitting the OOM within 7 days. Now I switched to 36gb one, and the RAM usage is creeping slowly to the limit (as it was in 24gb node).. Ie a few days ago it was 31gb, now 32. Im running it for 2 weeks now, but guess it will be killed because of OOM soon.\".\r\n\r\nThe reason behind is that user is running `trace_call` for each pending transaction on node.\r\nThis leads to high usage of memory which may stop our node because of OOM exception (to be checked on testnodes)\r\n",
